                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/793.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>, representing
                        American interests in Mexico, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>59. American Society of Mexico requests me to forward following to the
                    Department: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>Tax decree August 31, quoted by Silliman, temporarily reduces exorbitant
                            amount of former decrees but levy is still most excessive, because, as
                            Silliman fails to state, the six pesos per pertenencia is now
                            collectible in Mexican gold worth from seven to nine times the Carranza
                            paper money of enforced circulation. Positively majority mine owners
                            cannot pay, which will result confiscation of properties. We strongly
                            urge representations against any increase in mine taxes.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
